I just want to learn about mechanical cuckoo clocks but the entire first few pages of search results are of shops selling clock parts.

I search videos on YouTube and there are web ads at the top of the list before even the first actual video thumbnail.

What the fuck.

stories.text:
I understand that Amazon is huge and that many buys their goods from them. What I fail to understand is why. When I go to my country's (SE) Amazon page's listings I mainly see irrelevant products with machine translated nonsense for descriptions.

What is the enormous selling points that I am missing when I'm faced with this confusing mess?

I'm not trying to crack down on the company here, I just don't understand why they are the best.
stories.title: Ask HN: What Is the Appeal of Amazon?
